This means when `compression` is set to `COMPRESSION_LEVEL.uncompressed`, the mutated code will NOT use the `store: true` archiver option, but instead will use the default zlib compression path. This will result in a compressed zip file rather than an uncompressed one.

The key observable difference: an uncompressed zip should be larger than a compressed zip of the same content. The existing test `'ZIP test folder using compression rate'` already tests this by comparing file sizes. I need to write a focused test that specifically checks this behavior.

